{"word":"H2560 - חָמַר - châmar - khaw-mar' - Daub","slug":"H2560","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">חָמַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>châmar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khaw-mar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Daub"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D7;&#x05DE;&#x05E8; - cha&#x0302;mar</b> - <i>khaw-mar'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>boil</i> up; hence to <i>ferment</i> (with scum); to <i>glow</i> (with redness); as denominative (from <a href=\"#/H2564\">H2564</a>) to <i>smear</i> with pitch: - daub, foul, be red, trouble."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2543\">H2543</a>, <a href=\"#/H2544\">H2544</a>, <a href=\"#/H2566\">H2566</a>, <a href=\"#/H3180\">H3180</a>"}]}